Why no separate ECR credential needed

aws ecr get-login-password   ← uses AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID + AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
        │
        ▼
returns a temporary docker token (valid 12 hours)
        │
        ▼
docker login --password-stdin   ← uses that token
        │
        ▼
docker push to ECR   ← authenticated

------------------------------------
So aws-creds-uat and aws-creds-prod you already created — those are your ECR credentials too. Nothing extra to store.
--------
Single quotes in sh don't expand variables — switch to double quotes or triple-quote sh \"\"\". Then pass ${params.ENV} to --namespace and kubectl config use-context so the same stage deploys to UAT or PROD based on what was selected at build time. 
Add a when { expression { params.ENV == 'prod' } } approval stage before deploy for safety.
